entère en tomodensitométrie multidétecteurs</a></div><div class="related__authors"><ul class="rlist--inline loa mobile-authors loa-height"><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">L. Gengler</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">M.-N. Roedlich</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">B. Sauer</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">C. Balzan</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">N. Holl</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">F. Veillon</span></li></ul></div><div class="meta">2008Dec1 | Feuillets de Radiologie, Vol. 48, No. 6</div></div><div class="getFTR external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0181-9801(08)74638-4">Crossref</a></div></div></li><li class="citedByEntry" data-doi="10.2214/AJR.07.3347"><div class="related"><div class="related__title"><a target="_blank" href="https://doi.org/10.2214/AJR.07.3347">MDCT Evaluation of Blunt Abdominal Trauma: Clinical Significance of Free Intraperitoneal Fluid in Males with Absence of Identifiable Injury</a></div><div class="related__authors"><ul class="rlist--inline loa mobile-authors loa-height"><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">T. Eric Drasin</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Stephan W. Anderson</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Amy Asandra</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">James T. Rhea</span><span>, </span></li><li><span class="hlFld-ContribAuthor">Jorge A. Soto</span></li></ul></div><div class="meta">2008Dec1 | American Journal of Roentgenology, Vol. 191, No. 6</div></div><div class="getFTR external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.2214/AJR.07.3347">Crossref</a></div></div></li><li class="citedByEntry" data-doi="10.1148/radiol.2492072055"><div class="related"><div class="related__title"><a target="_self" href="/doi/full/10.1148/radi